# Data — large datasets and model caches stay out of git.
# Small metadata files at data/external/ root (corpus_stats.json,
# eval_subset.csv, corpus_inventory.csv) ARE intentionally tracked
# as derived inputs to downstream phases.
data/raw/
data/processed/*
data/interim/
data/telugu-ocr/
data/external/*
!data/external/*.json
!data/external/*.csv
!data/external/README.md
# The frozen evaluation subset (~30 page images + their ground-truth .txt
# files) IS intentionally tracked. It's the canonical eval set every
# downstream phase scores against; teammates should not regenerate it
# locally or it would drift between runs.
!data/external/eval_subset/
!data/external/eval_subset/**
# The Phase 4 scoring CSV (per-page CER/WER for each model x preprocessing
# cell) IS tracked. It is a small metadata artifact downstream phases and
# the final report depend on; regenerating it requires the full OCR matrix
# on disk, which is large and gitignored. Carve-out the parent directory
# so git will recurse into it.
!data/processed/eval_subset/
!data/processed/eval_subset/cer_wer.csv
# Everything else inside data/processed/eval_subset/ (the per-cell OCR
# output directories and their manifest.jsonl files) stays gitignored
# because those are large and regenerable.
data/processed/eval_subset/*/
*.csv.gz
*.parquet
*.h5
*.hdf5
*.npy
*.npz
*.pkl
*.pickle

